 Tributes have poured in to former Cathkin High pupil Maggie Quinn who was killed at a disturbance at a flat on Skye Road.   Maggie Quinn, 36, died after the incident which took place on the street in the early hours of Friday morning. 
A man was also injured and is being treated at a hospital in the city.
Friends of the mum of four – who was unemployed – paid tribute to her.
One pal, who did not wish to be identified, said: “It is a shocking tragedy.
“Maggie was a bubbly outgoing person.
“It still has not sunk in properly.
“I’ve not been told or heard what happened.
“I’m still trying to come to terms with this news. It’s devastating.
“She had four children.”
Stunned friends flocked to social media to express their grief.
Erin McCartney posted on Facebook: “R.I.P Maggie. Can’t believe you’re gone.
“I hope you’re looking down on me and looking after me as always. Love you forever.”
Katrina Tolmie wrote: “Miss you like mad, hen. Love you forever and always. RIP.”
 
A police spokesperson had confirmed that an investigation was underway following the incident.
A man appeared in court on Monday (June 15) charged with murder
Craig Simpson made no plea or declaration when he appeared in private at Glasgow Sheriff Court.
The 35-year-old, of Rutherglen, was also charged with assault to severe injury and attempted murder.
He was committed for further examination and remanded in custody.
A 26-year-old man was injured in the same incident on Skye Road in the early hours of Friday.
He remained in hospita.
